1
00:00:10,967 --> 00:00:11,933
I'm sorry.

2
00:00:12,067 --> 00:00:13,400
From what I've seen,

3
00:00:13,533 --> 00:00:16,233
it seems that everything
dad told me wasn't true.

4
00:00:16,367 --> 00:00:17,433
Mookie!

5
00:00:17,567 --> 00:00:20,533
How does it feel to be rejected
again by your own child?

6
00:00:20,667 --> 00:00:22,133
A police officer
is waiting outside.

7
00:00:22,267 --> 00:00:24,867
They can't find out
about Ligaya. Hurry up!

8
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:26,600
They sensed
what we were about to do.

9
00:00:26,733 --> 00:00:28,000
They took Ligaya.

10
00:00:28,133 --> 00:00:34,267
I don't need a sibling,
much less a mother!

11
00:00:34,433 --> 00:00:35,667
I'll support you
in whatever makes you happy.

12
00:00:35,800 --> 00:00:37,200
Thank you for understanding.

13
00:00:37,333 --> 00:00:38,633
Boss...

14
00:00:38,767 --> 00:00:40,433
did I hear it right?

15
00:00:40,567 --> 00:00:41,533
Are you letting her go?

16
00:00:41,667 --> 00:00:43,767
I'm not dumb to let Emma go.

17
00:00:43,900 --> 00:00:44,800
Ador!

18
00:00:44,933 --> 00:00:45,867
Ador!

19
00:00:46,967 --> 00:00:48,433
I'm giving you up.

20
00:00:48,567 --> 00:00:49,233
Thank you, Jade.

21
00:00:49,367 --> 00:00:51,100
My future plans

22
00:00:51,233 --> 00:00:55,067
will make him forget Emma
without me having to lift

23
00:00:55,200 --> 00:00:58,067
a perfectly manicured finger.

24
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:49,067
Is that Danilo calling?

25
00:01:51,700 --> 00:01:52,833
It's okay.

26
00:01:52,967 --> 00:01:54,300
Answer it.

27
00:02:00,400 --> 00:02:01,700
Hello, Dan?

28
00:02:15,133 --> 00:02:17,933
Will you let yourself
get defeated?

29
00:02:21,900 --> 00:02:22,700
How about you?

30
00:02:26,533 --> 00:02:28,267
Danilo called off the wedding.

31
00:02:29,333 --> 00:02:31,967
He admitted that he was
still in love with Emma.

32
00:02:35,933 --> 00:02:37,733
Emma admitted
the exact same thing.

33
00:02:39,367 --> 00:02:41,300
She's still in love with Danilo.

34
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:45,600
Danilo belongs to me.

35
00:02:45,733 --> 00:02:48,500
And Emma belongs to you.

36
00:02:48,667 --> 00:02:51,333
So, I think we need
to join forces.

37
00:02:52,433 --> 00:02:55,167
We need to stop them
from getting back together.

38
00:02:59,333 --> 00:03:00,933
What's your plan?

39
00:03:23,067 --> 00:03:24,033
Here you go.

40
00:03:24,167 --> 00:03:25,867
Boss Logan wants you
to have this.

41
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:27,400
To calm you down.

42
00:03:27,533 --> 00:03:31,500
He said you've been restless
after you talked to Danilo.

43
00:03:32,933 --> 00:03:33,800
You know what?

44
00:03:33,933 --> 00:03:36,633
I find Boss Logan weird.

45
00:03:36,767 --> 00:03:40,500
He totally supports
you and Danilo.

46
00:03:40,633 --> 00:03:42,667
As I told you,
Logan is a good person.

47
00:03:42,800 --> 00:03:44,533
Tell him my thanks.

48
00:03:44,667 --> 00:03:46,367
I really need this.

49
00:03:46,500 --> 00:03:48,133
Relax!

50
00:03:48,267 --> 00:03:49,167
Come on.

51
00:03:49,300 --> 00:03:50,433
You know what?

52
00:03:50,567 --> 00:03:54,100
I really hope Danilo believes
everything you say.

53
00:03:57,067 --> 00:03:59,067
He will believe me.

54
00:03:59,200 --> 00:04:03,133
Especially when I show him the
findings from Dr. Samson.

55
00:04:05,267 --> 00:04:05,933
Well, then.

56
00:04:06,067 --> 00:04:07,467
Good luck!

57
00:04:07,600 --> 00:04:08,667
You've got this!

58
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:09,800
Stay there.

59
00:04:09,933 --> 00:04:11,333
Get some beauty rest.

60
00:04:11,467 --> 00:04:13,833
I'll wait for Danilo
and Mookie outside, okay?

61
00:04:13,967 --> 00:04:15,667
Drink it all up
for you to calm down.

62
00:04:15,800 --> 00:04:16,567
Relax.

63
00:04:52,433 --> 00:04:53,433
Emma?

64
00:04:57,200 --> 00:04:58,233
Dan?

65
00:05:01,233 --> 00:05:02,467
Ems.

66
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:03,633
Dan.

67
00:05:03,767 --> 00:05:04,700
Emma!

68
00:05:09,033 --> 00:05:12,033
I think I got drunk
from the wine Logan gave me.

69
00:05:12,167 --> 00:05:13,367
It's okay.

70
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:19,200
<i>We need to prevent them
from getting back together.</i>

71
00:05:19,333 --> 00:05:22,500
<i> I heard Danilo and Mookie.</i>

72
00:05:22,633 --> 00:05:27,900
<i>They were planning
to meet with Emma.</i>

73
00:05:28,033 --> 00:05:31,867
<i>So that's why Danilo
called her.</i>

74
00:05:33,167 --> 00:05:35,800
<i> So, I think...</i>

75
00:05:35,967 --> 00:05:38,033
<i>you're going to be needing this.</i>

76
00:05:40,567 --> 00:05:42,100
<i> What's this?</i>

77
00:05:42,233 --> 00:05:43,400
<i> Hallucinogen.</i>

78
00:05:44,500 --> 00:05:45,600
<i> You're welcome.</i>

79
00:05:49,267 --> 00:05:50,267
<i> Oh, by the way...</i>

80
00:05:51,300 --> 00:05:53,333
<i> it works perfect with wine.</i>

81
00:05:58,867 --> 00:06:00,567
You look so beautiful today.

82
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:04,600
I miss you so much, Emma.

83
00:06:05,833 --> 00:06:06,600
Dan.

84
00:06:07,467 --> 00:06:10,000
Dan, I miss you so much, too.

85
00:06:10,133 --> 00:06:11,700
I miss you so much.

86
00:06:14,167 --> 00:06:15,900
Hey, Sir.
How's everything going?

87
00:06:16,033 --> 00:06:17,067
Do we have
a lot of guests already?

88
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:18,167
Yes, Ma'am.

89
00:06:18,300 --> 00:06:19,200
Okay.

90
00:06:19,333 --> 00:06:22,033
Sir, check him thoroughly.

91
00:06:23,400 --> 00:06:25,167
That's a little too much, Sir.

92
00:06:25,300 --> 00:06:26,367
- Please put that down.
- There.

93
00:06:26,500 --> 00:06:27,467
Flor?

94
00:06:28,300 --> 00:06:29,233
Mookie!

95
00:06:29,367 --> 00:06:31,067
Danilo!

96
00:06:31,200 --> 00:06:33,633
Flor is loud, as always.

97
00:06:33,767 --> 00:06:35,133
Don't be too mean.

98
00:06:35,267 --> 00:06:37,633
- Joke only.
- Let it slide, I'm just happy.

99
00:06:37,767 --> 00:06:40,033
Wait, where's Emma?

100
00:06:40,167 --> 00:06:42,333
She's in the office
waiting for you.

101
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:45,067
Listen. I can't go
with you inside.

102
00:06:45,200 --> 00:06:46,733
But I'll tell you where to go.
Okay.

103
00:06:46,867 --> 00:06:48,733
Go straight all the way
to the end.

104
00:06:48,867 --> 00:06:50,033
Then turn left.

105
00:06:50,167 --> 00:06:53,700
You'll see a glass door,
that's the office.

106
00:06:53,833 --> 00:06:54,800
- Okay, Flor.
- Okay, okay.

107
00:06:54,933 --> 00:06:56,033
Did you get it?

108
00:06:56,167 --> 00:06:57,233
- Thank you, Flor.
- Thank you.

109
00:06:57,367 --> 00:06:58,233
Okay, go ahead.

110
00:06:58,367 --> 00:06:59,433
-I'm sorry, I can't go with you.
-It's okay.

111
00:06:59,567 --> 00:07:02,400
Sir, let them in.
They are Emma's guests.

112
00:07:02,533 --> 00:07:03,667
- Let's go, Dear.
- Okay, bye.

113
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:05,000
Come on, Dad.

114
00:07:33,333 --> 00:07:34,233
Mom?

115
00:07:39,567 --> 00:07:40,700
Darn you!

116
00:07:49,367 --> 00:07:51,433
I think someone else is here.

117
00:07:51,567 --> 00:07:53,600
- It's embarrassing.
- No, it's okay.

118
00:07:53,733 --> 00:07:55,567
It's okay, no one's here.

119
00:07:56,767 --> 00:07:57,700
No one.

120
00:08:38,667 --> 00:08:39,633
Jade...

121
00:08:41,167 --> 00:08:42,267
mission accomplished.

122
00:08:43,667 --> 00:08:45,667
Well done, partner.

123
00:08:45,800 --> 00:08:47,367
<i> But I didn't get enough.</i>

124
00:08:48,533 --> 00:08:49,733
Emma fell asleep.

125
00:08:50,633 --> 00:08:53,267
I put all the capsules
in her wine.

126
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:55,367
So what if she fell asleep?

127
00:08:55,533 --> 00:08:57,367
Continue with what you're doing.

128
00:08:57,500 --> 00:08:59,600
Don't forget
to record it on video.

129
00:08:59,733 --> 00:09:01,567
We will send it to Danilo.

130
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:04,100
Do you want me to take advantage
of someone sleeping?

131
00:09:04,233 --> 00:09:06,100
Do you think I'm a rapist?

132
00:09:06,233 --> 00:09:07,500
Then don't.

133
00:09:07,633 --> 00:09:09,100
Chill.

134
00:09:09,233 --> 00:09:11,333
Do you know what to do?

135
00:09:33,067 --> 00:09:34,200
Yes?

136
00:09:37,033 --> 00:09:38,800
Do you want to say something?

137
00:09:42,833 --> 00:09:44,567
You're so desperate.

138
00:09:47,033 --> 00:09:48,867
To be honest...

139
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:50,633
you're pitiful.

140
00:09:52,933 --> 00:09:56,867
Evil will never succeed, Olive.

141
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:58,033
Nope.

142
00:09:58,933 --> 00:10:00,433
I'll succeed.

143
00:10:01,100 --> 00:10:03,433
Danilo will marry me.

144
00:10:03,567 --> 00:10:10,000
And we will be a one big
happy family with Mookie.

145
00:10:11,067 --> 00:10:13,233
I know, I know, I know.

146
00:10:13,367 --> 00:10:17,333
It's just too bad that
you won't be able to see it.

147
00:10:21,333 --> 00:10:22,367
Oh, well.

148
00:10:24,233 --> 00:10:25,300
That's life.

149
00:10:38,500 --> 00:10:39,167
Mookie.

150
00:10:39,300 --> 00:10:40,967
Mookie, are you okay?

151
00:10:41,100 --> 00:10:42,267
Are you okay?

152
00:10:44,267 --> 00:10:45,400
I'm okay now, Dad.

153
00:10:48,800 --> 00:10:50,300
I don't get it.

154
00:10:50,433 --> 00:10:51,700
I don't understand, Mom.

155
00:10:51,833 --> 00:10:53,933
She told us she and Logan
were not in a relationship.

156
00:10:54,067 --> 00:10:55,967
But what did we see?

157
00:10:57,133 --> 00:10:58,800
I don't know either.

158
00:10:58,933 --> 00:11:01,900
I have no idea.
I also can't understand.

159
00:11:02,033 --> 00:11:03,067
Come on, Dad.

160
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:05,033
Let's go to mom.

161
00:11:05,167 --> 00:11:07,567
We need to hear her explanation.

162
00:11:07,700 --> 00:11:08,500
Let's go!

163
00:11:08,667 --> 00:11:10,433
What explanation
do you want to hear?

164
00:11:11,700 --> 00:11:13,200
You saw it clearly.

165
00:11:13,333 --> 00:11:14,900
She's kissing Logan.

166
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:18,500
What else do you want to know,
Mookie?

167
00:11:20,333 --> 00:11:22,500
It's clear as the sky!

168
00:11:22,633 --> 00:11:24,933
Your mom is fooling us.

169
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:29,433
My only mistake is...

170
00:11:29,567 --> 00:11:32,233
I believed and trusted your mom.

171
00:11:35,967 --> 00:11:38,233
I wish even though
I missed your mom so much...

172
00:11:41,533 --> 00:11:43,833
I wish I had held my ground.

173
00:12:34,467 --> 00:12:35,300
Mommy!

174
00:12:35,633 --> 00:12:36,533
Jade!

175
00:12:36,667 --> 00:12:38,167
Wait! Wait!

176
00:12:38,300 --> 00:12:40,100
- What are you doing?
- I want to die!

177
00:12:40,233 --> 00:12:41,300
Wait, wait.

178
00:12:41,433 --> 00:12:43,967
- Jade, put that down.
- No! No!

179
00:12:44,100 --> 00:12:46,767
I want to take my own life!

180
00:12:46,900 --> 00:12:48,200
I love you, Dan.

181
00:12:49,500 --> 00:12:52,433
You're the only man
I love this much.

182
00:12:52,567 --> 00:12:53,833
And Mookie...

183
00:12:56,133 --> 00:12:58,600
I love Mookie so much.

184
00:12:58,733 --> 00:13:02,567
Not just as a niece,
but like my own child.

185
00:13:05,200 --> 00:13:07,267
She made me feel like a mother.

186
00:13:09,033 --> 00:13:10,867
- I'm done!
- Jade! Jade! Hold on!

187
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:12,867
No! Leave me alone, Dan!

188
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:14,000
Get out here! Leave me alone!

189
00:13:14,133 --> 00:13:16,400
- I'm sorry, Jade.
- Leave me be!

190
00:13:16,533 --> 00:13:18,967
Don't move, wait, Jade.

191
00:13:20,533 --> 00:13:21,733
Let me get this.

192
00:13:23,967 --> 00:13:25,033
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

193
00:13:26,033 --> 00:13:26,967
I'm sorry.

194
00:13:31,767 --> 00:13:33,567
Jade, I'm sorry.

195
00:13:33,700 --> 00:13:35,200
I made a mistake.

196
00:13:38,467 --> 00:13:39,900
Jade...

197
00:13:40,033 --> 00:13:40,900
let's push through
with the wedding.

198
00:13:41,033 --> 00:13:43,000
Isn't that what you like?

199
00:13:43,133 --> 00:13:43,867
No.

200
00:13:45,733 --> 00:13:46,967
You're only saying that

201
00:13:47,100 --> 00:13:49,267
because you don't want me
to harm myself.

202
00:13:50,300 --> 00:13:51,867
But the truth is...

203
00:13:52,967 --> 00:13:54,967
you're still in love with Emma.

204
00:13:59,700 --> 00:14:02,100
I'm done! Get out of here!

205
00:14:02,233 --> 00:14:03,767
Leave me alone!

206
00:14:08,800 --> 00:14:10,100
Jade, listen.

207
00:14:11,633 --> 00:14:14,300
Emma doesn't deserve my love.

208
00:14:16,667 --> 00:14:18,633
Believe me, Jade.

209
00:14:24,600 --> 00:14:25,600
Why?

210
00:14:27,233 --> 00:14:28,767
What happened, Dan?

211
00:14:28,933 --> 00:14:30,233
Did...

212
00:14:30,367 --> 00:14:32,533
did Emma do something again?

213
00:14:39,900 --> 00:14:42,533
I don't want to talk
about that woman anymore.

214
00:14:43,600 --> 00:14:44,933
She's an evil woman.

215
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:47,667
For me...

216
00:14:47,800 --> 00:14:49,800
she's already dead.

217
00:14:51,333 --> 00:14:53,033
So stop crying.

218
00:14:54,633 --> 00:14:56,167
We'll push through
with the wedding.

219
00:14:57,600 --> 00:14:59,167
- Okay?
- Really?

220
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:02,200
I love you, Dan.

221
00:15:03,833 --> 00:15:05,567
I love you so much.

222
00:15:09,900 --> 00:15:10,567
Mookie!

223
00:15:10,700 --> 00:15:11,633
Mookie, come.

224
00:15:11,767 --> 00:15:12,767
Join us.

225
00:15:12,900 --> 00:15:14,167
- Come here.
- Come here.

226
00:15:15,467 --> 00:15:17,500
Come here, Mookie, dear.

227
00:15:53,033 --> 00:15:56,733
I'm sorry, Anne, if I had
to ask you to come here.

228
00:15:56,867 --> 00:15:59,600
There's a little changes
in the wedding.

229
00:15:59,733 --> 00:16:02,300
No problem, Miss Jade. Anytime.

230
00:16:02,433 --> 00:16:03,500
It's a good thing

231
00:16:03,633 --> 00:16:06,067
that I haven't taken back
the invitations yet, Jade.

232
00:16:06,200 --> 00:16:08,233
I'm glad to hear that.
Thank goodness for that.

233
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:10,167
Anyway, about the changes.

234
00:16:10,300 --> 00:16:12,900
There's a little adjustment
regarding the time.

235
00:16:13,033 --> 00:16:14,400
Sure.

236
00:16:23,067 --> 00:16:24,633
Dad.

237
00:16:24,767 --> 00:16:26,033
Isn't it too early for that?

238
00:16:27,667 --> 00:16:29,200
You're drinking already?

239
00:16:30,433 --> 00:16:32,800
This is just my third bottle.

240
00:16:32,933 --> 00:16:33,833
But...

241
00:16:33,967 --> 00:16:35,833
this will be the last.

242
00:16:35,967 --> 00:16:37,533
Last, for now.

243
00:16:38,800 --> 00:16:40,633
Dad, is this the right thing
for you to do?

244
00:16:41,700 --> 00:16:43,767
Will you really push through
with the wedding?

245
00:16:43,900 --> 00:16:45,367
Or are you just doing this

246
00:16:45,500 --> 00:16:49,433
because Aunt Jade
threatened to kill herself?

247
00:16:49,567 --> 00:16:51,900
Or maybe it's because
you're mad at mom?

248
00:16:53,133 --> 00:16:54,200
You know what, Mookie?

249
00:16:55,233 --> 00:17:00,767
Even before we caught
your mom with Logan...

250
00:17:01,833 --> 00:17:04,200
I was determined to marry Jade.

251
00:17:06,033 --> 00:17:09,233
It's just that Emma fooled me
when we were in the forest.

252
00:17:10,300 --> 00:17:11,967
That's why I changed my mind.

253
00:17:12,767 --> 00:17:15,067
You saw it, right?

254
00:17:15,233 --> 00:17:16,933
How she hurt me?

255
00:17:18,433 --> 00:17:19,400
Dad...

256
00:17:20,367 --> 00:17:22,267
I'm upset with mom, too.

257
00:17:23,600 --> 00:17:27,400
But I hope you give
your decision some thought.

258
00:17:27,533 --> 00:17:31,067
Why do you sound like...

259
00:17:31,200 --> 00:17:33,367
you don't want me to push
through with the wedding?

260
00:17:35,467 --> 00:17:37,200
Don't you like your Mommy Jade?

261
00:17:40,600 --> 00:17:42,167
It's not like that, Dad.

262
00:17:43,233 --> 00:17:44,600
But...

263
00:17:44,733 --> 00:17:48,033
I've just noticed recently that
she has a lot of red flags.

264
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:52,300
She wasn't yelling at me before,
but now she does.

265
00:17:52,433 --> 00:17:54,400
She reminds me of Mommy Olive.

266
00:17:56,600 --> 00:17:58,467
And you know what, Dad?

267
00:17:59,767 --> 00:18:00,967
When she heard

268
00:18:01,100 --> 00:18:02,733
that you wanted to push through
with the wedding,

269
00:18:02,867 --> 00:18:04,867
I saw her smirked.

270
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:07,267
And she was crying
but there was no tears.

271
00:18:30,467 --> 00:18:31,867
Gosh...

272
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:33,467
it's so tiring.

273
00:18:34,400 --> 00:18:36,367
Ouch. My body aches.

274
00:18:36,500 --> 00:18:39,800
The bar has been crowded
for two nights now.

275
00:18:39,933 --> 00:18:42,567
We're so busy
that we couldn't even talk.

276
00:18:44,267 --> 00:18:45,433
By the way, what happened?

277
00:18:45,567 --> 00:18:48,433
How did your meeting
with Danilo and Mookie go?

278
00:18:48,567 --> 00:18:49,767
Tell me something.

279
00:18:51,267 --> 00:18:53,100
Honestly, Flor,

280
00:18:53,233 --> 00:18:54,867
I can't remember anything.

281
00:18:56,533 --> 00:18:58,733
But Danilo came.

282
00:18:58,867 --> 00:18:59,567
And...

283
00:19:01,400 --> 00:19:02,433
we...

284
00:19:03,933 --> 00:19:05,467
we kissed.

285
00:19:07,533 --> 00:19:07,900
And then...

286
00:19:08,600 --> 00:19:10,333
I fell asleep.

287
00:19:11,433 --> 00:19:15,800
Maybe I got drunk from the wine
that Logan gave me.

288
00:19:15,933 --> 00:19:18,867
What a bummer.
It could've been perfect,

289
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:21,333
but the wine messed it up.

290
00:19:21,467 --> 00:19:24,067
But you're unbelievable!

291
00:19:24,200 --> 00:19:26,333
You kissed in front of Mookie?

292
00:19:26,467 --> 00:19:28,900
- Hey!
- Didn't you get embarrassed?

293
00:19:29,067 --> 00:19:31,467
Wait. Mookie wasn't there.

294
00:19:31,600 --> 00:19:32,767
It was just Danilo.

295
00:19:33,800 --> 00:19:35,233
What are you talking about?

296
00:19:35,367 --> 00:19:38,600
I greeted both of them
when they arrived.

297
00:19:38,733 --> 00:19:40,967
I just couldn't go with them.

298
00:19:41,100 --> 00:19:45,267
I saw them coming here before
I entertained the customers.

299
00:19:45,400 --> 00:19:46,633
What are you saying?

300
00:19:46,767 --> 00:19:49,200
That's impossible.
Danilo came alone.

301
00:19:49,333 --> 00:19:52,833
- Mookie wasn't there.
- They were together.

302
00:19:52,967 --> 00:19:54,733
Why do you insist that Danilo's
alone?

303
00:19:54,867 --> 00:19:56,633
Wait.

304
00:19:56,767 --> 00:20:01,467
You're sure
that Mookie wasn't with Danilo.

305
00:20:01,600 --> 00:20:04,433
But I'm sure
that she was with him.

306
00:20:07,133 --> 00:20:08,200
I don't get it.

307
00:20:10,400 --> 00:20:11,800
- Why is that?
- You know what...

308
00:20:11,933 --> 00:20:14,233
you better call Danilo.

309
00:20:14,367 --> 00:20:16,200
To know the truth.

310
00:20:16,333 --> 00:20:17,433
And so we can understand

311
00:20:17,567 --> 00:20:19,933
why we have two different
versions of what happened.

312
00:20:20,067 --> 00:20:22,167
I'm waiting for his message.
But he hasn't texted me yet.

313
00:20:22,300 --> 00:20:24,867
So I didn't send him a message,
too.

314
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:26,800
He didn't?

315
00:20:26,933 --> 00:20:29,267
Why is that so? It's weird.

316
00:20:29,400 --> 00:20:30,467
You know what?

317
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:31,667
I feel like...

318
00:20:31,800 --> 00:20:36,800
there could be an anomaly
that night.

319
00:20:36,967 --> 00:20:38,067
What could it be?

320
00:20:39,333 --> 00:20:41,533
Well, I also don't know.

321
00:20:45,333 --> 00:20:47,133
I have an idea.

322
00:20:47,267 --> 00:20:49,067
Let's check the CCTV.

323
00:20:50,033 --> 00:20:53,500
There's no CCTV here
in the office.

324
00:20:53,633 --> 00:20:56,000
I'm referring
to the CCTV outside.

325
00:21:02,233 --> 00:21:04,833
I'm worried about dad.

326
00:21:04,967 --> 00:21:07,633
He's been drinking for days.

327
00:21:07,767 --> 00:21:12,067
I feel that he's just forcing
himself to marry Aunt Jade

328
00:21:12,233 --> 00:21:14,400
because he's mad at mom.

329
00:21:14,533 --> 00:21:16,067
And he wants to get even.

330
00:21:17,233 --> 00:21:19,133
There goes Danilo again.

331
00:21:19,267 --> 00:21:21,767
What did Ligaya say about that?

332
00:21:21,900 --> 00:21:25,333
I'm sure your grandmother
is furious.

333
00:21:25,467 --> 00:21:27,500
That's also the problem.

334
00:21:27,633 --> 00:21:29,100
I tried to call Grandmother

335
00:21:29,233 --> 00:21:31,833
because I needed someone
to talk to.

336
00:21:31,967 --> 00:21:34,233
But I couldn't contact her.

337
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:38,267
Are you able to call her?

338
00:21:38,400 --> 00:21:40,100
Do you talk to her?

339
00:21:40,233 --> 00:21:44,133
I really need her right now.
I need someone to talk to.

340
00:21:44,300 --> 00:21:47,100
We also can't reach her, Mookie.

341
00:21:47,233 --> 00:21:48,333
What?

342
00:21:48,467 --> 00:21:50,633
We thought you had
communicated with her.

343
00:21:50,767 --> 00:21:53,167
- Yes.
- No.

344
00:21:53,300 --> 00:21:55,733
When she went back to Cebu,

345
00:21:55,867 --> 00:21:58,200
that was the last time
I heard about her.

346
00:21:58,333 --> 00:22:01,267
So, when she flew back
to Cebu...

347
00:22:02,933 --> 00:22:04,667
she never reached out to you?

348
00:22:07,033 --> 00:22:10,000
Are you sure Ligaya's in Cebu,
Mookie?

349
00:22:10,133 --> 00:22:12,567
That's what Mommy Jade said.

350
00:22:17,033 --> 00:22:18,167
Why?

351
00:22:19,367 --> 00:22:21,400
It's just that...

352
00:22:21,533 --> 00:22:25,200
we feel something strange
with Jade.

353
00:22:25,333 --> 00:22:27,433
The last time we talked...

354
00:22:27,567 --> 00:22:28,900
Ligaya said something.

355
00:22:30,033 --> 00:22:31,600
<i> I was shocked.</i>

356
00:22:31,733 --> 00:22:33,433
<i>She didn't act like Jade at all.</i>

357
00:22:33,567 --> 00:22:35,233
<i> She yelled at me.</i>

358
00:22:35,367 --> 00:22:36,600
<i> She reminded me of Olive.</i>

359
00:22:36,733 --> 00:22:39,433
<i> Olive was so like that.</i>

360
00:22:39,567 --> 00:22:41,633
Isn't that what you
also noticed, Mooks?

361
00:22:41,767 --> 00:22:43,000
When Aunt Jade yelled at you,

362
00:22:43,133 --> 00:22:45,500
you told me
she was like your Mommy Olive.

363
00:22:45,633 --> 00:22:47,200
You experienced the same thing,
Mookie?

364
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:50,333
Yes.

365
00:22:50,467 --> 00:22:52,567
Wait, wait.

366
00:22:52,700 --> 00:22:56,033
Jade was the last person
Ligaya talked to.

367
00:22:56,167 --> 00:22:57,533
- Correct?
- Yes.

368
00:22:58,700 --> 00:23:00,167
Don't you think that witch

369
00:23:00,300 --> 00:23:01,400
did something
to your grandmother?

370
00:23:18,867 --> 00:23:21,333
Why was Logan the one
who came in after you left?

371
00:23:21,500 --> 00:23:23,067
No, it was Danilo.

372
00:23:23,200 --> 00:23:24,633
It was Danilo who came inside.

373
00:23:24,767 --> 00:23:26,433
Danilo again.

374
00:23:26,567 --> 00:23:27,467
How can it be Danilo?

375
00:23:27,600 --> 00:23:29,733
You can clearly see
that it's Boss Logan.

376
00:23:29,867 --> 00:23:31,700
And I just left.

377
00:23:31,833 --> 00:23:34,500
Danilo couldn't come
right after.

378
00:23:34,633 --> 00:23:36,667
Forward it.

379
00:23:41,933 --> 00:23:44,300
There! I told you!

380
00:23:44,433 --> 00:23:46,933
Danilo and Mookie were together.

381
00:23:48,267 --> 00:23:49,167
How did that happen?

382
00:23:49,300 --> 00:23:50,967
Come on, Emma.

383
00:23:51,100 --> 00:23:52,233
What did you have?

384
00:23:52,367 --> 00:23:55,900
You seemed hallucinating.

385
00:23:59,500 --> 00:24:00,400
<i> Here.</i>

386
00:24:00,533 --> 00:24:02,400
<i>Boss Logan wants you
to have this.</i>

387
00:24:02,533 --> 00:24:03,833
<i> So you can relax.</i>

388
00:24:03,967 --> 00:24:08,000
<i>He said you've been restless
after talking to Danilo.</i>

389
00:24:11,300 --> 00:24:12,400
The wine.

390
00:24:13,267 --> 00:24:15,333
The wine that Logan sent me.

391
00:24:26,533 --> 00:24:27,600
Love, here's your beer.

392
00:24:27,733 --> 00:24:29,000
Thank you.

393
00:24:29,167 --> 00:24:30,300
Mommy Jade,

394
00:24:30,433 --> 00:24:31,967
I'm just curious.

395
00:24:32,100 --> 00:24:34,067
Who will walk you to the altar?

396
00:24:34,200 --> 00:24:35,133
I wish it was you.

397
00:24:35,267 --> 00:24:36,433
But then...

398
00:24:36,567 --> 00:24:39,400
you're already
my maid of honor, so...

399
00:24:39,533 --> 00:24:41,700
I'll just walk down
the aisle alone.

400
00:24:41,833 --> 00:24:44,800
Why not Grandmother Ligaya?

401
00:24:45,933 --> 00:24:47,533
Can we stop talking
about that woman?

402
00:24:47,667 --> 00:24:49,300
Jade, Jade, Jade!

403
00:24:49,433 --> 00:24:51,733
What did you do at the bar
when Danilo went there?

404
00:24:51,867 --> 00:24:53,567
What's going on? What did I do?

405
00:24:53,700 --> 00:24:55,367
You sent me some wine.

406
00:24:55,500 --> 00:24:57,833
You put something on that wine.
What is it?

407
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:03,433
Hello?

408
00:25:05,567 --> 00:25:06,867
Is anyone there?

409
00:25:09,200 --> 00:25:10,200
Grandmother!

410
00:25:10,333 --> 00:25:11,700
Grandmother, is that you?
